Movie is a $250k budget with no CGI at all, it's all makeup, special effects, modeling and some other stuff. It was really gorey than the last one. It was longer than the first by about a hour. Acting was better and killing was more creative. I like it that is had unbelievable swearing, which it make it so real, because most horror films have a limited swearing, but this one has unlimited. I like the dialogue a lot, because what they say is what they would say irl, which makes the film more real. The characters were smarter than the avg people in horror movies, but were still what some dumb. I like how this movie takes place in current events, while the first one was taken in the past. The movie was really met for our generation and I really like about that. And the clown really lives up to his name. For my comments for it are "This movie will slash you away" "A piece of art" and "A slasher movie for the young generation". I like this movie better than Black Adam, which was 195-200m budget movie as this one was a 250k budget movie. It proves that higher budget movies can not always be good.
